# Books Management API - Authentication HTTP Calls

### Variables
@host = http://127.0.0.1:8000
@username = httptestuser
@password = httptestpassword

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###

### 2. Log in (Obtain access and refresh tokens)
# Note: FastAPI OAuth2PasswordRequestForm expects application/x-www-form-urlencoded
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username={{username}}&password={{password}}

###

### 3. Refresh Access Token
# Replace "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE" with the refresh token from the login response
POST {{host}}/api/v1/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}
